race.description: Community Bank Fleurieu-Bendigo Bank Mdn Plate
race.comment: IT'S ONLY MAGIC (3) brings the best, having run well in several stronger metropolitan maidens. Overall, he's placed in three of his nine starts and looks capable of handling most of his rivals here. With tactical speed and a low draw, Campbell Rawiller will have a few options and can get him home. ZADOWS LANDING (5) has improved with each run this preparation and might be ready to peak for this. Murtagh sticks and he's run well at the track previously. HEAT OF THE NIGHT (8) is another improver second-up and out to 1350m. She did enough at the end of her first-up run to suggest she's come back well. EAGLE MOON (2) comes back to SA after a midfield finish in Victoria. Drawn well and will roll forward so may give some cheek, while FISSIONABLE (6) is a first-starter that has jumped out OK and deserves some thought.
